RACE.FOOTNOTES: OSCAR WINNER ran just off the early pace, made a move after the 8th hurdle, and extended away. GREYLOVER ran with the leaders but lacked a late response to finish second best. THOMOND PARK maintained position mid-pack and was outpaced in the final half mile. WORLD OF FOOLS ran mid-pack early, fell behind, and trailed. UNDERCOVER ROWDY (IRE) led through eight hurdles, tired, pulled up and walked off. POINT OF GRACE was never a factor, tired, and pulled up before second to last and walked off. BIG RED CARDINAL was never a factor, pulled up after the 6th hurdle and walked off.

The highest rated horse will be assigned 158 lbs. with all other weights adjusted accordingly based on the current ratings. Minimum weight 140 lbs., not including apprentice allowances.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOOROO (IRE) ran slow early, moved up inside to track the pace, made move at the 7th hurdle, and pulled away to win handily. DURRAGH (IRE) tracked the leaders, made move at the 7th hurdle to challenge the leader but weakened in the stretch. SENOR SEVILLE was behind early and was never a threat, weakening two fences out. JUNONIA exchanged the lead the first mile with BELLA COOLA, weakened, tired and pulled up before the last, and walked off. BELLA COOLA dueled the first mile, weakened, tired and pulled up before the last and walked off. THREE O ONE showed brief speed, dropped back, tired and pulled up two from home and walked off.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PING PONG CHAMP tracked the lead early, maintained the pace, and assumed command 1/2 mile out. FEARSOME (GB) ran mid pack behind the leaders, progressed after the 7th hurdle, but was outrun to be second best. NEW APPOINTMENT (IRE) progressed steadily early, held a brief lead, leveled out, and was outrun in the stretch. YANKEE DOODLE BOY ran off the pace for the first mile, made a move after the 8th hurdle, then leveled off. ANTICIPATING always ran behind, ran evenly, but had no response. SEA MAST ran behind early, made steady progress, but weakened in the final 1/2 mile. CIRCUS led through the first five hurdles, faded quickly, tired and pulled up. SPEED ALERT showed a dull effort, suffered an injury, pulled up after the 8th, and was vanned off.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FAMILY TREE (GB) ran last early, made headway at fence 11, assumed the lead after fence 12 and was driven to the finish.
